complete_model_interaction.output:
The essence of the model is that responders compare the monetary offer (split_self) to a notion of fairness that is derived from their contribution relative to the combined contribution (token_self and token_opp). Specifically, the fair share is computed as the ratio of the participant's tokens to the total tokens multiplied by the combined earning. If the offered amount is lower than this fair share then the responder experiences a fairness violation that reduces the utility of accepting the offer. The utility of accepting an offer is thus a combination of the monetary gain offered plus an overall intercept (θ) minus a penalty (α) proportional to how much the offer falls short of the fair share. There are only two learnable parameters: the disadvantageous inequity aversion (α) and the baseline bias (θ). This parsimony is also aimed at reducing covariance between parameters during recovery testing.

<MODEL>
U = theta + split_self - alpha * max((token_self/(token_self+token_opp))*combined_earning - split_self, 0)
</MODEL>

<VARIABLES>
