A fairness-based utility model for responders in the Ultimatum Game that computes the utility of accepting an offer by comparing the monetary offer to a fair share based on contributions. A penalty for receiving less than the fair share is imposed via disadvantageous inequity aversion (alpha), with an additional baseline bias parameter (theta) that shifts overall utility.
</SUMMARY>

